One of a kind Peabody carbine. It was completely disassembled , cleaned, inspected and lubed. It was then converted from 50 rimfire to 56/50 by replacing the block and hammer. All the original parts are included with the carbine so it can be returned to as issued configuration .

Looking to sell my M70. I've owned it for roughly two years now.
As soon as I got it home I stained the wood furniture back to the reddish/ brown color with a dim coat of gloss. Otherwise it was just bare wood. You can see where the Cosmoline soaked into the stock and discolored it a bit.
Being an M70 it does have the canted sight. It's hard to see unless you know what you're looking for. Even with the canted sight, believe it or not; this rifle can out-shoot my AR.
